<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62c5f944-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3746"><num value="3746">§ 3746.</num><heading> Tribal immunity</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to affect, modify, diminish, or otherwise impair the sovereign immunity from suit enjoyed by Indian tribes.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62c5f945-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/177/tIII/s306">Pub. L. 103–177, title III, § 306</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/103/435/s12/b">Pub. L. 103–435, § 12(b)</ref>, <date date="1994-11-02">Nov. 2, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4572">108 Stat. 4572</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
